  "response": "No, the full test taker report (including detailed performance data) is *not* accessible immediately after the GMAT.\n\nImmediately after you complete the GMAT at the test center, you will see an **unofficial score report** on the screen. This report shows your:\n\n*   Verbal score\n*   Quantitative score\n*   Integrated Reasoning score\n*   Total GMAT score (out of 800)\n\nThis is *not* the official score report, but it's a very good indication of what your official score will be.\n\nThe **official score report**, which includes your AWA score and a more detailed breakdown of your performance, will be available on the GMAC website within 3-5 business days and sent to you officially around 15-20 days later.\n\nThe **detailed test taker report** that provides insights into your strengths and weaknesses, and helps you understand the areas where you need to improve, is made available within a few days.\n",
